        "title": "How do you add dependencies to google dataflow?",
        "body": "<p>I am trying to add opencv to a data-flow project. And from what I have read, all you should have to do is add the opencv jar and it will be uploaded to the staging bucket. But I know that cant be all (mostly doesn't work). I get the following error when I try to run my code as a direct pipeline on my local machine.<\/p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p><code>Exception in thread \"main\" java.lang.UnsatisfiedLinkError: org.opencv.videoio.VideoCapture.VideoCapture_1(Ljava/lang/String;)J\n    at org.opencv.videoio.VideoCapture.VideoCapture_1(Native Method)\n    at org.opencv.videoio.VideoCapture.&lt;init&gt;(VideoCapture.java:40)<\/code><\/p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>I have read this post,\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/39465128/how-do-i-add-java-dependencies-to-a-google-dataflow-project\">How do I add Java dependencies to a Google Dataflow project?<\/a> , but all it says it to add the jar to the classpath. Which doesnt work. I am missing something obvious I feel.<\/p>\n",
