        "creation_date": 1489690522,
        "body": "<p>UnsatisfiedLinkError is:\nThrown if the Java Virtual Machine cannot find an appropriate native-language definition of a method declared native.\n<a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/UnsatisfiedLinkError.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/lang/UnsatisfiedLinkError.html<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>Since the issue is occurring when you build/run locally, it is not related to the Dataflow Service or uploading to a staging bucket.<\/p>\n\n<p>A quick Google search for \"opencv UnsatisfiedLinkError\" brought up many results.  The most common response was that this line is missing:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>static {\n  System.loadLibrary(Core.NATIVE_LIBRARY_NAME);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
